# Styling & Tailwind Standards

## Responsive Design (Mobile-First)
- Base classes must always target mobile devices [3].
- Use responsive modifiers (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) only to add or override styles for larger screens.
- ❌ `className="w-[1200px] md:w-full"`
- ✅ `className="w-full md:w-[1200px]"`

## Interactive States (a11y)
- Every interactive element (button, link, input) must have explicit `:focus` and `:hover` states [3].
- Ensure focus rings are visible for keyboard navigation.
- ✅ `className="hover:bg-blue-600 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:outline-none"`

## Magic Numbers
- Avoid arbitrary values (e.g., `h-[432px]`) [4].
- Use Tailwind's spacing and sizing scale whenever possible.